<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-210] Clarify Jobstats documentation and add ALPS environment variable</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-210</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cray&apos;s Application Level Placement Scheduler (ALPS) now sets an environment variable identifying the running application.  That environment variable is ALPS_APP_ID.  This needs to be documented in section 12.1.1 of the Lustre Manual.  A row for ALPS should be added to the table in that section.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In addition, the table and its description are somewhat misleading.  It sounds like the value of jobid_var can &lt;b&gt;only&lt;/b&gt; be one of the values listed in the table, which is not true.  The table just contains special values for the jobid_var and examples of the environment variables set by some job schedulers.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The table should be split into two tables, and the columns should be swapped.  The first table should have a correspondence between job schedulers and environment variables.  The second table should contain the two special values: procname_uid, and disable.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The description preceding the first table should read something like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The following table shows the environment variables which are set by various job schedulers.  Set jobid_var to the value for your job scheduler to collect statistics per job.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The description preceding the second table should be something like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;This table shows two special values for jobid_var and their effects.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="22350">LUDOC-210</key>
